  "hmrcQuote": "The maximum available residence nil rate band in 2020 to 2021 is £175,000, but since the flat left to the son is only worth £100,000, only £100,000 of the tax-free residence allowance applies. The remaining residence nil rate band of £75,000 is available to transfer to the husband's estate."
